# Defence-in-depth — private cosign keys MUST never enter the repo.
# The Z2 real-cosign proof generates keypairs in tmp_path + wipes
# the private key after signing; this .gitignore covers the case
# where a future maintainer accidentally writes a key into the
# integration test dir (or switches to a fixture-based approach
# per the plan's Step 1 Option (b) and forgets the file hygiene).
*.key
*.pem
